  "prompt": "Are there any antibiotics that can be purchased over the counter?",
  "response": "In most countries, antibiotics are not available over the counter and require a prescription from a healthcare provider. This is because misuse and overuse of antibiotics can lead to antibiotic resistance, making infections harder to treat in the future. Some topical antibiotics, such as creams or ointments for minor cuts and scrapes, might be available without a prescription, but oral antibiotics typically are not. It's important to consult a healthcare professional for appropriate diagnosis and treatment of bacterial infections.",
